Hey everyone, welcome to my latest time-lapse video! In this one, I’ll be illustrating a fashion design while also showing you a technique for correcting the skewing that often occurs when you draw at an angle. As you’ll see, I was able to fix the elongation of the model’s features, specifically the hat and the chin, resulting in a more accurate representation. Plus, I composed the music for this video too! Hello and welcome to my latest fashion illustration video! In today’s tutorial, I’m going to show you how to hold a pencil at a different angle to create a variable line. This technique will allow you to add depth and dimension to your illustrations by creating thick and thin lines on the same stroke. Using this method, you can easily depict the folds and drapes in clothing, making your illustrations appear more realistic and detailed.

I understand that learning this technique can be a bit tricky, so I’ve taken the time to make this video a little longer than usual. By doing this, I can break down the process and give you a clear understanding of how to achieve those beautiful variable lines in your fashion illustrations.

As an added bonus, I’ve included one of my original songs in the video to help set the mood and inspire your creativity.

If you enjoy this video, please follow, like, and comment. Your support means the world to me, and I look forward to bringing you more fashion illustration tutorials in the future.

Welcome to this mesmerizing time-lapse video where you get to witness the creation of a stunning illustration inside a digital environment. Using my trusty iPad and the Procreate app, I delve into the world of digital art, immersing myself in the possibilities of this versatile medium. One of the reasons I love drawing digitally is the ability to zoom in and out, enabling me to see the illustration in all its intricate details.

In this video, I also showcase a technique I previously demonstrated in a different video, where I hold the pencil sideways to create thicker and thinner lines. You’ll see how this technique adds depth and intensity to the illustration, bringing it to life in a unique way.

So, sit back and enjoy this creative journey as I bring my imagination to life on a digital canvas. And if you want to check out that previous video and more of my work, head over to my Instagram @byelaineleon.

Welcome to this timelapse video of a fashion illustration created by me! PLEASE FORGIVE THE BLURRINESS! For this artwork, I used a Palomino Pearl pencil, which is a fantastic tool for smooth writing and strong line work. Fun fact: these pencils were the favorite of Chuck Jones, the creator of Bugs Bunny. I paired my Palomino pencil with a kneaded eraser, which allows for gentle erasing without rubbing the paper.
Drawing is a daily practice for me, and while this may not be my favorite piece, I believe that each illustration helps me improve. As always, at the end, I corrected the skewing on the face. I was sitting at an angle again! I’m also excited to share that I composed the music in this video!
Thank you for taking the time to watch my process. Be sure to check out the hashtags below to see more of my work and other artists in the fashion illustration community.

🎥 Hello everyone!! I’ve got an exciting video tutorial to share with you all! 🎨 So, here’s the deal: I was in New York when I got hit with a nasty bout of sickness. At first, I brushed it off, thinking it was no biggie. But man, oh man, was I wrong! 😵 My sleep was wrecked for three whole months because of this persistent cough. Worried sick it might be Covid, I finally decided to get checked out. I was hoping for the best (just allergies, maybe?), but deep down, I feared the worst. Turns out, it wasn’t allergies or the dreaded virus—it actually required some antibiotics. Who saw that coming? 😮 Anyway, after being down and out for what felt like forever, I’m thrilled to say I’m back in action and ready to draw up a storm! Get ready for some seriously fun stuff coming your way! 🌟 Stay tuned, folks, ‘cause I’ve got a bunch of awesome projects cooking up, including my work from the past two years... you won’t want to miss it! 😉 #FashionIllustration #ArtisticComeback #HealthJourney #WatercolorMarkersRock #VideoTutorialFun #CreativeVibes #ArtProjectsGalore #FashionInspiration ##FashionIllustration #FashionArtist #FashionSketching #TimelapseArt #WatercolorMarkers #ArtTutorial #FashionInspiration #CreativeProcess #ArtisticJourney

🌹 Moving through #grief and #loss has been a journey of both sorrow and growth. Some losses were beyond my control, while others stemmed from embracing my #trueself and seeking healing and faith. My therapist once shared that #assertiveness might seem like aggression to those used to my people-pleasing ways. But I've come to realize that if someone left me at my lowest, they were never a true friend. Today, I find #closure in knowing I deserve better. 🌱 Remember, people-pleasing can lead to an early grave, so let's embrace our authenticity and prioritize our well-being. Dr. Gabor Mate's insightful video opened my eyes to this truth. 🙏 #EmbracingChange #HealingJourney #Authenticity

In this video, I present my original music score, Twinkle, accompanied by a visually stunning music video created using AI imagery and motion. I created the score in 2018 but never released it until now. As much as I love working with AI, it is never a replacement for the effort, nuances, and originality that humans have. Software like Illustrator and Photoshop became popular, and designers and artists were often asked if the software made their work or if they did. Having software on your computer without interacting with it does not produce artwork. AI borrows from art where humans become inspired and composite works, but AI by itself cannot accomplish the things humans can. AI needs human interaction to create beautiful imagery, and my works are no exception. I hope you enjoy the video!
